SMART PARKING LOT SYSTEM
=======================

OVERVIEW
--------
This C++ console application simulates a smart parking lot management system with real-time 
slot allocation, entry/exit tracking, and dynamic fee calculation.

KEY FEATURES
------------
1. 🅿️  Dynamic Slot Allocation (First-available algorithm)
2. ⏰ Real-time Entry Time Recording using <ctime>
3. 💰 Fee Calculation: $2 first hour + $1 per additional hour
4. 📊 Real-time Status Monitoring & Occupancy Statistics
5. 🚗 Vehicle Entry/Exit Management
6. 🔍 Available Slot Display

PROGRAM FLOW
------------
1. Initialize ParkingLot with capacity (10 slots)
2. Main Menu Loop:
   - Park Vehicle → Find available slot → Record entry time
   - Exit Vehicle → Calculate duration → Compute fee → Free slot
   - Display Status → Show all slots with occupancy details
   - Show Available Slots

CLASS STRUCTURE
---------------
ParkingSlot Class:
- Properties: vehicleNumber, entryTime, occupied status
- Methods: parkVehicle(), exitVehicle(), calculateFee()

ParkingLot Class:
- Properties: vector<ParkingSlot>, capacity
- Methods: parkVehicle(), exitVehicle(), displayStatus()

FEE CALCULATION ALGORITHM
-------------------------
fee = 2.0 + max(0, hours-1) * 1.0
Where hours = difftime(currentTime, entryTime) / 3600.0

SAMPLE EXECUTION
----------------
See 03_Test_Report/Example_Execution.txt

COMPILATION
-----------
g++ -o parkinglot main.cpp ParkingLot.cpp

RUN
---
./parkinglot